    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1833"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1833">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.11/77.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 326.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 21, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Supplementing my despatch of yesterday<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d1833fn1">Not printed.</note> concerning the arrangements made for
                    the protection of the foreign residents of Constantinople and their interests, I
                    have the honor herewith to transmit a list<note n="1" xml:id="d1833fn2">Not
                        printed.</note> of the forces landed from the neutral war vessels now in the
                    harbor in accordance with the decision of the Diplomatic Body, on the morning of
                    the 18th instant. About 2,500 men have been debarked with some 26 guns.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. W. Rockhill.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
